The paper presents a new algorithm for indexing large genome collections, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The focus on memory efficiency and speed suggests a potential application in computational biology and bioinformatics (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the use of the index for pattern matching, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
